<item>
            <title>[WICKET-3908] Encoding problem with POSTing a form with Ajax</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-3908</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The form is always posted using Ajax in UTF-8, but if you&apos;re using a different encoding in the DB or the HTML aswell, the string is ugly obviously. Wicket should convert from UTF-8 to the given encoding (detecting from getMarkupSettings().setDefaultMarkupEncoding(&quot;...&quot;); or getRequestCycleSettings().setResponseRequestEncoding(&quot;...&quot;); or an other settings parameter which could be given to wicket)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m attaching a quickstart project which demonstrate this issue by echoing back the string given to a textarea.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
